HEADWORD: Incommodity
<hw>In`com*mo"di*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Incommodities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>incommoditas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incommodit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Incommodious</er>.]</ety> <def>Inconvenience; trouble; annoyance;
disadvantage; encumbrance.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Bunyan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A great <qex>incommodity</qex> to the body.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Buried him under a bulk of <qex>incommodities</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

